cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.GR (Computer Graphics): The paper focuses on using probabilistic inference algorithms to constrain procedural models in computer graphics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper introduces neurally-guided procedural models, which use neural networks to control how the procedural model makes random choices. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper evaluates the method on L-system-like models with image-based constraints. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper introduces a method that uses neural networks to guide procedural models and improve their efficiency. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): While not the main focus of the paper, the method involves creating software that combines procedural models and neural networks.
